# Frontend design — RNS POS design system

When working on the Angular client (`Client/`):

## Apply styling by default

- Implement UI using the design tokens and patterns from **`docs/design/interactive.html`**.
- Global styles live in **`Client/src/styles.scss`** (CSS variables, `.wf-*` utilities, shell layouts).
- Reuse shared components (`pos-button`, `confirm-dialog`, `copy-field`, `paginator`, `form-actions`, `async-shell`) — they carry the design system classes.
- Do **not** add UI libraries (Tailwind, Bootstrap, Angular Material) unless explicitly requested.

## Shell accents (per site)

| Shell | `data-shell` | Accent |
|-------|----------------|--------|
| Admin | `admin` | Violet |
| Platform | `platform` | Red |
| Kiosk | `kiosk` | Green |
| Kasse | `kasse` | Amber |

Wrap pages in the matching shell layout (e.g. `AdminLayout` for `/:slug/admin/*`).

## Markup conventions

- Lists: `.wf-table`, `.wf-badge`, `.wf-toolbar`, `pos-paginator`
- Forms: `.wf-form`, `.wf-fieldset`, `form-actions`
- States: `.wf-loading`, `.wf-empty`, `.wf-alert.error`
- Auth: `.auth-page` + `.auth-card`
- Buttons: `pos-button` or `.wf-btn` (+ `.primary`, `.danger`, `.ghost`)

## Scope

- Match existing patterns in neighboring pages before inventing new ones.
- Keep markup semantic; avoid inline `style` attributes.
- Consult `modern-web-guidance` skill for dialog, form, and layout CSS when unsure.
